title: Midnight Voyage 12-04-2008 - Dialectic Sines
description:
Another great live in studio DJ mix from Dialectic Sines. Heard originally on The Midnight Voyage on the night of 12-04-2008. You can hear a live DJ mix from Dialectic Sines on the show on the first Thursday of every month. Check out his music on his myspace page (/dialecticsines).

Check out The Midnight Voyage on the web to see full playlists from past shows and more. /midnightvoyage903 on Myspace!



Here&#039;s the setlist:


Shpongle - Shpongle Falls

Abakus - Daybreak

Vibrasphere - 102 Miles From Here

Haltya - Walking on Sunshine

More info about The Midnight Voyage:


The Midnight Voyage is an epic journey through the endless realm of electronic music. If you have the desire to feel the rhythm, to feel inspired by beautiful sounds, then tune into the show every Thursday night/Friday morning from 12 AM to 3 AM. It happens on 90.3 FM WUTK in Knoxville, TN broadcasting from the University of Tennessee. For those out of reach of the station, you can also tune it in online at www.wutkradio.com/listen. To listen, all you have to do is install either Real Player or Real Alternative.

You can download Real Alternative at the following link: <a href="
http://www.free-codecs.com/download_soft.php?d=4763&s=65" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.free-codecs.com/download_soft.php?d=4763&s=65</a>

On the show, you can hear a wide variety of electronic music both old and new, covering a vast array of sub-genres and styles. The main goal of the show is to provide listeners with creative, inspired electronic music in whatever form it may take, whether it makes you wanna get down, freak out, or just close your eyes and let it take you to that special place. The Voyage features psychedelic and experimental styles of music including trance, techno, breakbeat, drum n bass, house, industrial, downtempo/chillout, post-rock, and everything in between. Also, on the first show of every month, you can catch a live in-studio DJ set from local Knoxville artist Dialectic Sines, who brings the crazy psychedelic sounds that will warp your brain and take you to another dimension! Hear music by Dialectic Sines on his myspace page (/dialecticsines).

For those of you who aren&#039;t so genre-bent, some other artists/musicians you can hear on the show include:
